Module org.cumulus4j.annotation

	Annotations which can be used in the data model classes additionally to the JDO/JPA annotations
	in order to control the behaviour of Cumulus4j.

	See {{{../documentation/persistence-mapping.html}Persistence mapping}} for further details.

* Maven

	After adding the repositories documented on the {{{../download/index.html}Download}} page
	to your <<<pom.xml>>>, you can add the following dependency in order to use this module: 

+------------------------------------------+
<dependencies>
	...
	<dependency>
		<groupId>org.cumulus4j</groupId>
		<artifactId>org.cumulus4j.annotation</artifactId>
	</dependency>
	...
</dependencies>
+------------------------------------------+

	The above dependency does not (and should not!) declare a version. Instead, it is recommended that
	you add the following to your dependency-management:

+------------------------------------------+
<dependencyManagement>
	<dependencies>
		...
		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.cumulus4j</groupId>
			<artifactId>org.cumulus4j.parent</artifactId>
			<type>pom</type>
			<version>${project.version}</version>
			<scope>import</scope>
		</dependency>
		...
	</dependencies>
</dependencyManagement>
+------------------------------------------+

